# ToolMind — AI Tools Directory

## What this is
ToolMind is an AI tools directory web app. Users describe 
a task and instantly find the best AI tool for it.
Search, browse by category, compare tools side by side.

## Tech stack
- Next.js 14 App Router
- TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS
- Supabase (database + auth)
- Framer Motion (animations)
- Phosphor Icons (weight="thin" only)
- Geist + Geist Mono fonts

## Design system
- Background: #fafaf9 (off-white)
- Text: #0f0f0e (near-black)
- Border: 1px solid #e5e5e5
- Accent: #0f0f0e
- Card background: #ffffff
- Muted text: #6b6b6b
- FREE badge: bg #f0fdf4 text #166534
- FREEMIUM badge: bg #eff6ff text #1d4ed8
- PAID badge: bg #f9fafb text #374151
- Zero shadows anywhere — borders only
- Geist Display for headlines
- Geist Mono for tags, labels, prices
- Framer Motion on every page entrance
- Staggered fade-up, 0.6s ease out

## Folder structure
app/
  page.tsx — homepage with search
  search/page.tsx — search results
  tools/page.tsx — full directory
  tools/[slug]/page.tsx — tool detail
  compare/page.tsx — side by side compare
  category/[slug]/page.tsx — category view
components/
  ui/
    nav.tsx — floating pill navigation
    tool-card.tsx — tool card component
    search-bar.tsx — animated search bar
    category-pill.tsx — category filter pill
    pricing-badge.tsx — FREE/FREEMIUM/PAID
lib/
  supabase/
    client.ts — browser client
    server.ts — server component client
  data/
    categories.ts — category + tool seed data
styles/
  globals.css — CSS variables

## Database tables
categories: id, name, slug, description, tool_count
tools: id, name, slug, description, website_url, 
       logo_url, category_id, pricing_tier, 
       best_for[], tags[], rating, verified
tool_tasks: id, tool_id, task, match_score

## Key behaviors
- Search queries Supabase full text across 
  name, description, tags, best_for
- Category pages filter tools by category_id
- Compare page reads ?tools=slug1,slug2 from URL
- Task pills on homepage link to /search?q=task
- Tool cards link to /tools/[slug]
- "Visit Tool" button opens website_url

## Code rules
- Never use any type
- No inline styles — Tailwind only
- Every client component needs 'use client'
- Use next/image for all images
- Handle loading and error states always
- Mobile responsive — all breakpoints
- No console.log in production code
- Components max 150 lines, split if longer

## Icon rules
- Phosphor icons only, weight="thin"
- Arrows use → ↗ text symbols
- Category codes: W_ <> [] |> ~_ ?_ ## @_ (); 
- No lucide-react anywhere

## Agent behavior
- Never ask for permission
- Execute everything completely
- Make best judgment on ambiguous decisions
- Fix all TypeScript errors before finishing
- Run npm run dev to verify after changes